658
00:29:05.610 --> 00:29:07.920
You recommend he repeat this test

659
00:29:07.920 --> 00:29:09.810
at which of the following intervals?

660
00:29:09.810 --> 00:29:11.490
Yearly, three years,

661
00:29:11.490 --> 00:29:13.893
five years, or 10 years?

662
00:29:19.500 --> 00:29:20.333
Excellent.

663
00:29:20.333 --> 00:29:23.566
So there are seven ways that we can screen

664
00:29:23.566 --> 00:29:25.590
for colorectal cancer.

665
00:29:25.590 --> 00:29:27.090
And the current recommendation

666
00:29:27.090 --> 00:29:30.870
is we start screening at age 45.

667
00:29:30.870 --> 00:29:33.650
Both the AGA and the USPSTF say,

668
00:29:33.650 --> 00:29:35.700
in the general population,

669
00:29:35.700 --> 00:29:39.180
do not worry about what test is chosen.

670
00:29:39.180 --> 00:29:41.400
Just choose a test.

671
00:29:41.400 --> 00:29:43.203
There's three stool based.

672
00:29:44.040 --> 00:29:49.040
High sensitive fecal called blood test,

673
00:29:49.080 --> 00:29:51.870
the FIT test or the FIT-DNA test.

674
00:29:51.870 --> 00:29:53.940
FIT-DNA is the Cologuard.

675
00:29:53.940 --> 00:29:55.800
There are four direct visualizations.

676
00:29:55.800 --> 00:29:57.810
Colonoscopy, CT colonography,

677
00:29:57.810 --> 00:29:59.820
flex sig or flex sig with a FIT.

678
00:29:59.820 --> 00:30:00.900
Now some of you may be thinking,

679
00:30:00.900 --> 00:30:02.820
